title: Youtube Not Working on iMac M3 after upgrading
content:
Hello, I recently upgraded my iMac and have just ported everything over. Everything seems to be fine except I cannot get Youtube to load properly. Oddly if I google a youtube video it will take me to the video and play ot however I will not see comments, related vids and cannot make fullscreen.

Here are the steps I have taken so far:

  1. 1 Confirmed Youtube will work on Safari
  2. 2 Updated Firefox
  3. 3 Cleared Cache and Cookies
  4. 4 Checked the recommended performance settings option
  5. 5 Unchecked the recommended performance settings option
  6. 6 Confirmed videos still will not load in troubleshooting mode
  7. 7 I have no active add-ons running on the browser

Any help would be great!
creator: brianshanedrums

title: Firefox crashing after a few seconds upon startup
content:
This is my crash ID: bp-ff99f648-78ab-4cad-b1f5-7aaa70240902 I've already tried troubleshoot mode, same result. I do have a userContent.css file, but deleting it makes no difference, and I can think of no other major change I've made to my installation.

I would prefer not to have to reinstall Firefox.

title: Firefox
content:
Firefox freezes intermittently, and when I examine the situation with Windows' Task Manager, I see a large number of Firefox threads active while I have only two tabs in use, and memory usage running rapidly up to the 50-70% range (I have 16 GB). While I'm not qualified, it seems there may be a memory leak issue. The situation clears itself after a just few or a few tens of seconds, but then may recur within a minute or so. This started a few weeks ago, now happens almost daily and is making Firefox, my preferred browser, somewhat unusable.

My system: Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-4790 CPU @ 3.60GHz 64-bit operating system, x64-based processor Windows 10 Pro OS Build 19045.4842 Firefox Version 115? VPN Windscribe Version 2.10.16

content:

title: FF on windows too slow saving files
content:
Hello, This is on Win 11, always latest updates to win and FF.

For at least the past 9 months saving anything (web pages, files, etc.) is incredibly slow. I have filed bug reports but nothing back. After starting the save the wheel rotates for 1-2 minutes before finally waking up and saving. FF is completely frozen until its done.

On a second win 11 box, the download are fast but flagged as download failed but the file was actually downloaded

Anyone know anything about this? Like why or how to fix it.

I'm switching to Chrome until this is resolved but I hate Chrome so I hope it will not be a long wait.

Thank you all
creator: essin

title: Firefox error "Video unavailable This content isn't available".
content:
When ever I click on a youtube link I get a flash of the video and then "Video unavailable This content isn't available". But the video is clearly available as runs fine in other browsers. Since FF is my default browser this is a real pain and may force me to go to a different default browser which I don't want.

I have cleared the cache no change It does the same in incognito mode

Please help.

Thanks

title: Problemas ao utilizar o navegador
content:
Prezada equipe do Firefox,

Espero que esta mensagem os encontre bem. Sou um usuário do Firefox e gostaria de compartilhar algumas sugestões que, na minha opinião, poderiam melhorar a experiência de navegação.

Atualmente, quando abro links da minha barra de favoritos, o navegador me direciona automaticamente para cada um deles. Eu gostaria de ter a opção de abrir vários links em novas abas sem ser redirecionado imediatamente para cada um. Essa funcionalidade já está disponível em outros navegadores e, embora possa parecer simples, é algo que aprecio e que tornaria minha navegação mais eficiente.

OBS. Falo na hora de utilizar o scroll do mouse.

Outro problema que vejo é que, ao abrir um vídeo no navegador em tela cheia, a tela pisca, como se fosse um movimento de abrir e fechar os olhos de uma pessoa. Acredito que essa função poderia ser aprimorada; em vez de piscar, o vídeo poderia ser colocado em tela cheia de forma mais suave e direta.

Agradeço pela atenção e pelo excelente trabalho que vocês realizam. Estou ansioso para ver como o Firefox continuará a evoluir no futuro.

Atenciosamente,

title: YouTube UI sometimes freezes frequently (~ every 10 seconds) for 2-3 seconds
content:

When in this state, I can often notice it frequently: on hovering over buttons the UI does not highlight them, the video controls will not appear, or the page will not fill the screen on resize, can't click into search, etc. Basically just full page freeze except for media playback.

It's disappeared and come back a few times, but tends to be more often there than not. This occurs on every page of Youtube. I've tried disabling basically all my extensions and refreshing the page without any change.
